#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn2.22"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn2.22:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 2 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 2 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn2.22:0.2"
msgid "3. Nānātitthiyavagga "
msgstr "3. Various Sectarians "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn2.22:0.3"
msgid "22. Khemasutta "
msgstr "22. With Khema "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn2.22:1.1"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho khemo devaputto bhagavato santike imā gāthāyo abhāsi: "
msgstr "Standing to one side, the god Khema recited these verses in the Buddha’s presence: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn2.22:2.1"
msgid "“Caranti bālā dummedhā, "
msgstr "“Foolish and unintelligent people "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:2.2"
msgid "amitteneva attanā; "
msgstr "treat themselves like an enemy. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:2.3"
msgid "Karontā pāpakaṃ kammaṃ, "
msgstr "They do bad deeds "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:2.4"
msgid "yaṃ hoti kaṭukapphalaṃ. "
msgstr "with bitter fruit. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn2.22:3.1"
msgid "Na taṃ kammaṃ kataṃ sādhu, "
msgstr "It’s not good to do a deed "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:3.2"
msgid "yaṃ katvā anutappati; "
msgstr "after which you will regret. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:3.3"
msgid "Yassa assumukho rodaṃ, "
msgstr "you experience the result "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:3.4"
msgid "vipākaṃ paṭisevati. "
msgstr "weeping, with a tearful face. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.132, sc4
msgctxt "sn2.22:4.1"
msgid "Tañca kammaṃ kataṃ sādhu, "
msgstr "It’s good to do a deed "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:4.2"
msgid "yaṃ katvā nānutappati; "
msgstr "after which you’ll not regret. "

# NOTE: I don’t understand the word patita: can it really be derived from pacceti?
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:4.3"
msgid "Yassa patīto sumano, "
msgstr "you experience the result "

# NOTE: See BB on finishing the deva’s verses here.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:4.4"
msgid "vipākaṃ paṭisevati. "
msgstr "joyful, with a happy mind.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
#. VAR: Paṭikacceva → paṭigacceva (bj)
msgctxt "sn2.22:5.1"
msgid "Paṭikacceva taṃ kayirā, "
msgstr "“As a precaution, you should do "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:5.2"
msgid "yaṃ jaññā hitamattano; "
msgstr "what you know is for your own welfare. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:5.3"
msgid "Na sākaṭikacintāya, "
msgstr "A thinker, a wise one would not proceed "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:5.4"
msgid "mantā dhīro parakkame. "
msgstr "thinking like the cart driver. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
#. VAR: maṭṭhaṃ → panthaṃ (bj, pts1-2) | pasatthaṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn2.22:6.1"
msgid "Yathā sākaṭiko maṭṭhaṃ, "
msgstr "Suppose a cart driver leaves the highway, "

# NOTE: reading maṭṭha above.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:6.2"
msgid "samaṃ hitvā mahāpathaṃ; "
msgstr "so even and well compacted. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:6.3"
msgid "Visamaṃ maggamāruyha, "
msgstr "They enter upon a rough road, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:6.4"
msgid "akkhacchinnova jhāyati. "
msgstr "and fret when their axle breaks. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn2.22:7.1"
msgid "Evaṃ dhammā apakkamma, "
msgstr "So too, an idiot departs the good "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:7.2"
msgid "adhammamanuvattiya; "
msgstr "to follow what’s against the good. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:7.3"
msgid "Mando maccumukhaṃ patto, "
msgstr "Fallen in the jaws of death, "

# NOTE: See BB’s comments on the commentarial readings for this line. I f ind it odd, surely there should be a vairation to apply the metaphor properly. In the parallel in Mil for this, the readings are the same. But note that the parallels in Chinese and Skt omit the cart metaphor.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.22:7.4"
msgid "akkhacchinnova jhāyatī”ti. "
msgstr "they fret like their axle’s broken.”"

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
